        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0417.jpg" n="part3_p025.jpg" xml:id="img_0025" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part3_p025.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_25_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>412.
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>and an ability to look on THES basis into the humanistic values with a new eye. And weffenreamt
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>this, to a certain extent—it was possible to understand what happens in Greece or in Rome MüCH
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>better in the light of the conflicts of the social situation in the twenties and, before that, in Germany
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>and Europe generally.
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>Mevertheless the shortcoming remained, namely the limitation to upper classes. And how
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>strong this limitation was, I only learned when I came to this country, where the opposite difficulty
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>seems to prevail.
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>The second, [education] for skills, has a danger that it becomes an education of Kjustment.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_25_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>And it is not by chance that it was invented by the absolute state— The absolute state which wanted
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>to have skillful soldiers and skillfui industrial population. Absolutism introduced, from above,
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>industrial activities into the respective lountries, and of course it needed people who were able to
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>be taught the activities they had to perform in the context both of the military and the industrial
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/> Kntivities, and in the higher form also of some low lorministK estivities. The higher administration
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>was still in the hands of those who wereilucated humanistically.
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>I say the danger of this education is that it becomes an education to Kjustment. Adjustment
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_25_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>has two meanings: to overcome a-social tendencies which are simply negative, in a pupil; and to
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>introduce the pupil into the norms and conventions of a given society. The danger is that while
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>the teachers, especially in this country, try to adjust the children into the necessities of life,
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>the conconditional necessities—not to become an outlaw, etc., which is right—THEY ALSO adjust
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>to the conventions and take away from them the possibility to say No to ANY convention,
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>ne se
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>dʼune manière beaucoup dʼautres
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼun autre vie de ses
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>dʼune manière vieuse
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>Monsieur Mounard
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>est toujours
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_12" n="N012"/>dans le Comte de
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_13" n="N013"/>décrire, sont aussi les
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_14" n="N014"/>vous avez luisé
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_15" n="N015"/>cʼest à lire
               <lb facs="#facs_25_tr_2_tl_16" n="N016"/>Monsieur
            </p>
            
